The Minister of Health, Dr Zwelini Mkhize has confirmed today (Wednesday, 11 March) that six new Coronavirus (COVID-19) cases have been confirmed. This takes the total number of coronavirus positive patients in South Africa to 13. The six new cases are as follows: Gauteng: Four KwaZulu-Natal: One A 40-year-old male who had travelled to Portugal. He returned on 7 March. Western Cape: One A 36-year-old male who had travelled to multiple countries including Germany, Austria, Switzerland and Turkey. He returned to South Africa on 9 March. ” All the patients have now been advised and those who are symptomatic have started receiving treatment. Some of the patients are already in hospital while some, specifically those who are asymptomatic are in self quarantine. Contact tracing has also started for all these cases,” said Dr Mkhize. To date, 3642 tests have been conducted. Dr Mkhize said that more information relating to these cases will be communicated. Dr Mkhize requested that the privacy of the patients and their families continue to be observed by the media and the public. This is a developing story and updates will follow as events unfold.